name: Triceratops, Re-purposed Dinosaur Toy, ANY COLOR
description:
Triceratops is a genus of herbivorous ceratopsid dinosaur which lived during the late Maastrichtian stage of the Late Cretaceous Period, around 68 to 65 million years ago (Mya) in what is now North America. It was one of the last non-avian dinosaur genera to appear before the Cretaceous–Paleogene extinction event. The term Triceratops, which literally means "three-horned face," is derived from the Greek τρί- (tri-) meaning "three", κέρας (kéras) meaning "horn", and ὤψ (ops) meaning "face".

Perfect for adding a little whimsical color to an office or bedroom. 

Listing is for one Dinosaur only (CHOOSE COLOR). 

Also available in HOT PINK!
https://www.etsy.com/listing/117181923/pink-triceratops-re-purposed-dinosaur

Not recommended for kids as this toy has been painted and can become scratched if played with.

Paint is a high quality, durable, and finished with several coats of resilient scratch resistant clear coating. Protective layers ensure paint won't flake off or become "tacky" when handled. Outdoor safe in shaded areas!

This little guy stands about 2" (4.5 cm) tall and about 6" long.

name: Diplodocus Dinosaur Figurine, ANY COLOR, Repurposed Toy
description:
Diplodocus is among the most easily identifiable dinosaurs, with its classic dinosaur shape, long neck and tail and four sturdy legs. For many years, it was the longest dinosaur known. Its great size may have been a deterrent to the predators Allosaurus and Ceratosaurus: their remains have been found in the same strata, which suggests they coexisted with Diplodocus.

Perfect for adding a little whimsical color to an office or bedroom. 

Listing is for one Dinosaur only (Choose Color).

Not recommended for kids as this toy has been painted and can become scratched if played with.

Paint is a high quality, scratch resistant, glossy finish with several layers of clear protective coat. 

Stands about 2.5" tall and about 6" long.
